        <definition>void unload_plugin</definition>
        <argsstring>(IPindPlugin *plugin)</argsstring>
        <name>unload_plugin</name>
        <param>
          <type><ref refid="structIPindPlugin" kindref="compound">IPindPlugin</ref> *</type>
          <declname>plugin</declname>
        </param>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Release resources allocated allocated by <ref refid="group__PLUGIN_1ga841f2257a22717c7c4a016ff138dbee3" kindref="member">load_plugin()</ref>. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>This function is called by pind before unloading the plugin library. Resources allocated by the plugin itself either on call to <ref refid="structIPindPlugin_1affbc68373c264c50a64f0b9b063a7d47" kindref="member">IPindPlugin::init</ref>, or during plugin operations, should be released by <ref refid="structIPindPlugin_1a036601ad3630cf483571107c2c9c44ce" kindref="member">IPindPlugin::uninit</ref></para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername direction="in">plugin</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The plugin to unload. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
